      • pause

        void pause()
        Pause a running Job. The Job will stop running at the next opportunity and retain it's state so that it can be resumed.

      • step

        void step()
   throws java.lang.Exception
        Advances the Job one step. If the Job is not currently started this will start the Job first.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception

      • resume

        void resume()
        Resume a running Job. The Job will resume from where it was paused.

      • stop

        void stop()
        Stop a running Job. The Job will stop immediately and will reset to it's freshly loaded state. All state about parts already placed will be lost.

        void run()
